annotation.TEXT: Now here's the adjustment I mentioned earlier: I took out the goal tape and added an exit pipe at the end of the level, which will take me to a short room with a goal. This way I won't die.
Alright, it's boss time! Yes, I consider the level itself to be the boss of this challenge!
Unfortunately, when it gets too fast, the game won't let me jump, so...
Death!!! But, with the midway gate hit, I can restart from here and shoot for the goal next time!
Note: With a fast autoscrolling sprite active, even the goal can kill you!!! This is because Mario's victory march doesn't keep up with the autoscroll.
Power ups are always nice, if you can grab them.
Let's see if I can at least reach midpoint on my first try here.
Yes! I'm in!
Right here, if I didn't get into the pipe fast enough, I would've been doomed!
...the autoscroll will keep up with it, and...
However, when coming out of that pipe in YI2, you can survive by hitting the goal while you're on the right edge of the screen.
D'oh!!! That didn't go well at all!
Now, I'm going to take on Yoshi's Island 2!
And, for whatever reason, it's not dawning on me to use my reserve mushroom, which could be useful in getting past that Podoboo!
Uh... Actually, it's getting kind of fast!
Bye, Yoshi!
Let's try that again, shall we?
I need Yoshi because, while the game won't let me jump normally at ultra-fast speeds, I can Yoshi jump! This will be necessary at the end of this level.
This lava pit up ahead is tricky. Can I make it across?
Darn! Missed stomping the shell, which would've given me another 1-up. That's okay, though. I should have enough lives for now.
Nuts! I didn't get 50, so no bonus game for me this time.
This room is much easier than the first, with no tricky jumps, and a much easier to enter door at the end.
Another odd thing about the fast autoscroll: Depending on the number of screens in an area, it may or may not stop scrolling at the end! Be careful, or you may just fall into nothingness!
Also, Iggy's Castle ends with a single-screen boss fight, and therefore doesn't need adjusting either.
Whoa! Let's try not to lose Yoshi yet!
May as well get a 1-up while I'm here, too.
No, there's no way I can get anything from this Yoshi block. The autoscroll is way too fast at this point!
However, I didn't expect Yoshi to stomp that parakoopa while I was already on the ground! If I Yoshi jumped better, I could've made it a bit farther, but I don't think I would've finished the level!
Now, one thing you gotta watch out for are the fences. If you're clinging to a fence and the autoscroll pushes you to the left edge of the screen, it will kiiilllll yooouuu!
...I can get some more extra lives!
BGM: Final Fantasy VI - The Decisive Battle
Well, this isn't too bad...
Yoshi's Island 4 is a bit easier. I don't need Yoshi for it, and if I don't make a stupid mistake, I should be able to finish it on my first try!
BGM: Yoshi's Cookie - Battle Theme C (sped up)
Death BGM: Castlevania - Lost Life
...I made it this time! The next two jumps should be easier (with the autoscroll assisting you on the big one!), then you'll automatically hit the midway gate!

If you press up at the exact right time after midpoint (like I managed to do), you can enter the next room right away. If you miss, it's no big deal if you have another life. Entering that door is much easier starting from midpoint.
And then just thrash Iggy like usual and that's it! Challenge complete!
If I kick this shell at just the right time...
Nevertheless...
Alright, I can do this! Come on!
Have you noticed that the number "4000" doesn't want to appear there?
Now, I bet you went back and checked to see whether the "4000" was there or not!
Also, I could use some more lives, too.
I adjusted the end of YI3 the same way, but it's not needed in YI4, because that level already ends just like this!
BGM: Final Fantasy - World Map
You know what? I should be collecting these coins, since I'm close to getting a 1-up from them.
I don't know if ditching Yoshi there was absolutely necessary, but I didn't want to take any chances!
One level left, the castle. Can I clear it?
Looks like I made it to midpoint!
Alright, let's see if I can finish this level now!
Once again, power ups are nice if you can get them!
Unfortunately, this won't work in YI1 and YI3, so I had to make some adjustments to the ends of those levels, which you'll see eventually.
First, I'll want to start collecting some extra lives, because I'll probably need them!
Crap! I missed entering the pipe! Yeah, I'm boned.
A special SMW challenge by illusion115: Clear all the Yoshi's Island levels with medium or fast autoscrolling sprites added.
Gee, I hope I have enough lives! If I have to, I'll go back to YI2 to farm for more, but hopefully, it won't take that many tries!
Now I'm actually surprised that the screen stopped scrolling at the proper point here!
Going back here for yet another Yoshi, which I may or may not need this time.
Hi, Yoshi!
Whoa! Look out!!!
Now, I don't normally do level editing in my challenges, but this one sounded interesting. Medium autoscrolling sprites are kind of easy, though, so I'm going with the fast ones all the way!
To make things easier, I'll be going down this pipe here. This way the autoscroll speed will reset, and it'll keep things more manageable.
BGM: Zelda II - Battle (by I8Strudel)
Can I avoid a humiliating defeat this time? Let's find out!
...Death!!!
Outta the way, Chuck!
Next, I'll be going to Yoshi's Island 3, but first, I'm going to pick up a spare Yoshi in case I need it.
Next, let's get Yoshi! But, who knows how long I'll be able to hold on to him!
I'll just pick up a 1-up while I'm here. By the way, I put fast autoscrolling sprites in the side areas, too, in case you hadn't noticed.
Well hey there, Podoboo! How's it going?
Now I need a new Yoshi...
Almost there! Come on, I can make it!
Alright, now let's have some fun!
Yay, more lives! Who knows? I might need them for the castle...
Hi, Yoshi!
Bye, Yoshi!

In order to cross that lava pit, you need to get as close to the right edge of the screen as you can, jump as far as you can, then briefly grab the fence, then jump off it before the autoscroll kills you, and pray that you make it!
Hi, Yoshi!
At least I managed to hit the midway gate, though. I'll be coming back to this level later.
Alright, now that I have Yoshi, it's time to finish Yoshi's Island 1!
Will the third time be the charm?
Avoid the berries, or at the very least, have Yoshi's tongue reach out and eat them. If Yoshi stops to eat one because his mouth overlapped it, the autoscroll will kill you!
Hi, Yoshi!
Okay. If I can enter the pipe up ahead, it'll make things so much easier!
Alright! Just two more levels left! Oh by the way, I'm not bothering with the Yellow Switch Palace this time, since it's still a cakewalk.
Nuts! Almost.
Crap! The autoscroll got me that time. I don't think I was far enough to the right when I started.
